<br>
Has anyone run into this vendor, and have any idea where it is located?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/19/01 11:08:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=931.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gor Taku Vendor under Shadeweaver's?</span><hr size=1> I have found this place.  You would have to kill many many Shak Dratha to get them to sell to you.<br>
<br>
There is a blacksmith, a brewer, and some sort of training master, much like the ones of the Shar Vahl who have pupils standing nearby learning.<br>
<br>
The real question here is, who are the real enemy?  the Gor Taku seem to be in league with the Loda Kai brigands.  The Shak Dratha are hostile at first, but I have seen signs that tell me they hold some secrets to some interesting tradeskills, if you were to gain their trust.<br>
<br>
I continue to research the issue of the two odd races and their relation to the Loda Kai.<br>
 <p><b><i>Casben Lightfoot</i></b>, Grumpy ol' Rake from Tunare<br><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, cleric of the Tinker's Pride

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubaddanfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaddanFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 10:25:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=931.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gor Taku Vendor under Shadeweaver's?</span><hr size=1> No, using sneak you can probably buy from them right away.<br>
<br>
What's the location of these vendors, please?<br>
<br>
...as for who exactly the enemy is, well Gor Taku are leagued with the Loda Kai, and several quests encourage us to kill Loda Kai, so the decision is pretty much made for me.  I'm already KOS to Gor Taku.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubaddanfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaddanFV</A> at: 12/20/01 10:31:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 10:38:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=931.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gor Taku Vendor under Shadeweaver's?</span><hr size=1> <br>
Another possibility is to have a bard who is not KOS to use his faction song.  The bard can then buy the item and give it to you.<br>
<br>
You might have to use a non-Vah Shir bard to do it ... it looks like a lot of Vah Shir are going to be killing Lodi Kai just because they are there.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/20/01 6:46:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=931.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gor Taku Vendor under Shadeweaver's?</span><hr size=1> yes I'm sure the rogues and bards can sneak in there.  I don't have the location.  <br>
<br>
You can enter the caves at a spot where there are three guards with odd names, they are sometimes Gor Taku, and sometimes Shak Dratha.  <br>
<br>
Enter through that cave and turn left at the intersection.  continue straight and you will find the place I speak of.  If that's not good enough, explore a bit.  I found the place with ease.<br>
 <p><b><i>Casben Lightfoot</i></b>, Grumpy ol' Rake from Tunare<br><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, cleric of the Tinker's Pride

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubaddanfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaddanFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/01 10:42:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=931.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gor Taku Vendor under Shadeweaver's?</span><hr size=1> Thanks, I know the area you are talking about. <br>
<br>
As for &quot;finding it with ease', well only if you go in the right direction.  I entered at the poacher cave and went NORTH, and explored every single cavern but never found it.<br>
<br>
Apparently it's at the south end of the caverns.  I'll find it tonight.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/21/01 7:19:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=931.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gor Taku Vendor under Shadeweaver's?</span><hr size=1> I suppose it does get confusing with so many passageways out to the east and west side of the ridge.<br>
<br>
Baddan, I'm curious.  If you find anything interesting let us know, I'm debating whether to go after them or not.<br>
<br>
